Charles Eugene Lancelot Brown
Charles Eugene Lancelot Brown (17 June 1863 â€“ 2 May 1924) founded BBC Brown Boveri (later ASEA Brown Boveri) with Walter Boveri. He was born in Winterthur and was one of 6 children. His mother was Swiss and his father, the British engineer Charles Brown (1827-1905), was the founder of SLM - Schweizerische Lokomotiv- und Maschinenfabrik (Swiss Locomotive and Machine Works).


== Career ==
He attended the Engineering School of Winterthur. He worked at his father's factory and then became the director.


